name: inquiry
trans: an official effort to collect information

name: insulation
trans: a material that stops heat or sound from escaping or entering

name: triumph
trans: to win

name: rally
trans: to bring or come together in order to provide support or make a shared effort

name: requisite
trans: a thing that is necessary for the achievement of a specified end.

name: cable
trans: (a length of) wire, esp. twisted into thick, strong rope or used to carry electricity

name: disparate
trans: different in every way

name: utterly
trans: completely

name: catastrophic
trans: involving substantial damage or disastrous health problems

name: Set out
trans: to start an activity with a particular aim

name: tow
trans: to pull a car, boat, aircraft, etc., using a rope or a chain attached to another vehicle

name: transmit
trans: to send or give something

name: snap
trans: to break something quickly with a cracking sound

name: inexplicably
trans: for an unknown reason

name: compensate
trans: to pay someone money in exchange for work done, for something lost or damaged, or for some inconvenience

name: voltage
trans: the force of an electric current, measured in volts

name: indispensable
trans: too important not to have; necessary

name: flaw
trans: a fault or weakness, esp. one that happens while something is being planned or made and that makes it not perfect

name: perseverance
trans: continued effort and determination

name: vilified
trans: having one's reputation ruined; being spoken about in a bad way
